<h2>Tips for Using Drag-and-Drop Editors Effectively</h2>

<p>Follow these tips to get the best results from any drag-and-drop website builder.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Start with a template:</strong> Do not build from a blank canvas unless you have design experience</li>
  <li><strong>Keep it simple:</strong> Resist the urge to use every available element and animation. Clean, simple designs perform best</li>
  <li><strong>Check mobile view:</strong> Always preview and adjust your design on <a href="/blog/mobile-responsive-website-builders">mobile devices</a></li>
  <li><strong>Use consistent spacing:</strong> Maintain uniform gaps between elements for a polished look</li>
  <li><strong>Limit your fonts:</strong> Stick to two or three fonts maximum across your entire site</li>
</ul>

